## Agent Structure

Specialized agents defined in `.ai/agents/`:

### Analysis & Design
- **product-owner** - Business requirements, user stories
- **architect** - Architecture design, ADRs, validation
- **technical-writer** - Documentation, READMEs, guides
- **ux-designer** - UX/UI design, accessibility (WCAG 2.2 AA)

### Data & Persistence
- **database-engineer** - Migrations, schema, query optimization

### Implementation & Quality
- **tdd-developer** - TDD implementation (RED-GREEN-REFACTOR)
- **security-auditor** - OWASP compliance, vulnerability scanning
- **qa-engineer** - Test coverage (100/80/0), testing pyramid
- **performance-engineer** - Optimization, profiling, Core Web Vitals

### Operations & Observability
- **devops** - CI/CD, Git workflow, infrastructure
- **observability-engineer** - Metrics, logging, tracing

## Workflow

### Sequential (for new features)
1. **Analysis** -> @product-owner (user stories, criteria)
2. **Design** -> @architect + @ux-designer (ADRs, wireframes)
3. **Database** -> @database-engineer (if schema changes)
4. **Implementation** -> @tdd-developer (RED-GREEN-REFACTOR)
5. **Security** -> @security-auditor (OWASP check)
6. **Quality** -> @qa-engineer (coverage 100/80/0)
7. **Deploy** -> @devops (CI/CD, PR)

### Transversal (invoked when needed)
- @technical-writer - documentation at any step
- @observability-engineer - metrics and logging during implementation
- @performance-engineer - optimization when required

